        <div n="124-0203" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-124-0203-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-124-0203-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-124-0203-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">Written about the Year 1712.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-124-0203-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-124-0203-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-124-0203-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-124-0203-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-124-0203-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-124-0203-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-124-0203-line-1"><hi rend="display-initial">N</hi>OW hardly here and there a Hackney-Coach</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-124-0203-line-2"> Appearing, show'd the ruddy Morn's Approach.</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-124-0203-line-3"> Now <hi rend="underline">Betty</hi> from her Master's Bed had flown,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-124-0203-line-4"> And softly stole to discompose her own.</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-124-0203-line-5"> The slip-shod 'Prentice from his Master's Door</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-124-0203-line-6"> Had par'd the Dirt, and sprinkled round the Floor.</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-124-0203-line-7"> Now <hi rend="underline">Moll</hi> had whirl'd her Mop with dext'rous Airs,</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-124-0203-line-8"> Prepar'd to scrub the Entry and the Stairs.</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-124-0203-line-9"> The Youth <ref target="#spp-124-0203-footnote-1">1</ref><note place="foot" n="1" xml:id="spp-124-0203-footnote-1">To find old Nails.</note> with broomy Stumps began to trace</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-124-0203-line-10"> The Kennel-Edge, where Wheels had worn the Place.</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-124-0203-line-11"> The Small-Coal Man was heard with Cadence deep;</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-124-0203-line-12"> Till drown'd in shriller Notes of <hi rend="underline">Chimney-sweep</hi>.</l><l n="13" xml:id="spp-124-0203-line-13"> Duns at his Lordship's Gate began to meet;</l><l n="14" xml:id="spp-124-0203-line-14"> And Brick-dust <hi rend="underline">Moll</hi> had scream'd thro' half a Street.</l><l n="15" xml:id="spp-124-0203-line-15"> The Turnkey now his Flock returning sees,</l><l n="16" xml:id="spp-124-0203-line-16"> Duly let out a-Nights to steal for Fees.</l><l n="17" xml:id="spp-124-0203-line-17"> The watchful Bailiffs take their silent Stands;</l><l n="18" xml:id="spp-124-0203-line-18"> And School-boys lag with Satchels in their Hands.124-0203   </l></lg></div>
      </div>
